[[ This file is a syntax cookbook. Each [[...]] block is a Fountain NOTE. Open in any Fountain-aware editor or parse with FNScript. ]]


[[ ========== TITLE PAGE (above first blank line) ========== ]]

[[ Keys commonly used: Title, Credit, Author(s), Source, Draft date, Contact, Copyright. Multiple lines per key are allowed on the title page. ]]


[[ ========== BODY OPENER (after title page) ========== ]]

FADE IN:


[[ ========== SCENE HEADINGS ========== ]]

INT. COFFEE SHOP - DAY #1#

A normal interior slug with scene number at end.

EXT. PARKING LOT - NIGHT #2#

Exterior slug.

INT. WAREHOUSE - CONTINUOUS

Slug without scene number.

.INT. FORCED SLUG - ANY TIME

Leading dot forces a scene heading even if the line would otherwise parse as something else.

INT. KITCHEN - LATER #3#

EST. CITY SKYLINE - MAGIC HOUR

Establishing shot slug (EST.).

INT./EXT. TUNNEL - CONTINUOUS

Combined interior/exterior slug (I/E, INT/EXT, INT./EXT., etc. — see Fountain slug rules).

I/E. BORDER - DAY

Alternate combined form.


[[ ========== ACTION ========== ]]

Plain action is any paragraph that does not match a stronger rule.

!Forced action line — exclamation prefix forces ACTION even if the line looks like ALL CAPS.

Action can run several lines
when there is no blank line between them — soft line breaks merge into one action block until a blank line or a recognized cue.

*Italic*, **bold**, and _underline_ markers are preserved in the source for downstream renderers (inline emphasis).


[[ ========== CHARACTER & DIALOGUE ========== ]]

MARTA
Simple dialogue after a CHARACTER cue in ALL CAPS.

MARTA (O.S.)
(off-screen extension in parentheses)

MARTA (CONT'D)
(continued — extension text is convention, not parsed specially)

MARTA
(beat)
Parenthetical on its own line between CHARACTER and DIALOGUE.

MARTA
Dialogue can span
multiple lines until a blank line ends the block.

@McLowcase
Leading @ forces CHARACTER even if the name is mixed case.

@SOMEONE (V.O.)
Forced character with extension.

LEO
First speech.

LEO
(wry)
Parenthetical element: starts with ( after character, no blank line before it.

LEO
Second speech after parenthetical.

[[ In-dialogue blank: between the two dialogue lines below, the middle line is exactly two ASCII spaces (U+0020 twice) — merged into one Dialogue element in this parser. ]]

NINA
Dialogue line one.
  
Dialogue line two continues the same cue after the two-space-only line.


[[ ========== DUAL DIALOGUE ========== ]]

ADAM
Left column line one.

EVE ^
Right column — caret after the SECOND character's name marks dual dialogue.

ADAM
Left continues.

EVE ^
Right continues until the block ends.


[[ ========== LYRICS ========== ]]

~♪ Row, row, row your boat
~Gently down the stream

~Forced lyrics line even when not starting with a musical symbol


[[ ========== TRANSITIONS ========== ]]

CUT TO:

SMASH CUT TO:

FADE OUT.

>FORCED TRANSITION LINE

> OMITTED SEQUENCE

OUT OF HERE TO:

[[ Lines whose trimmed text ends in TO: parse as transitions. Known bare transitions include FADE OUT., CUT TO BLACK., FADE TO BLACK. ]]


[[ ========== CENTERED TEXT ========== ]]

> THE END <

> TITLE CARD TEXT <

> CENTERED ACTION LINE <

[[ Centered action: line starts with > AND ends with < on the same line. Same line without a closing < is a forced transition, e.g.: ]]

> THIS IS A FORCED TRANSITION NOT CENTERED


[[ ========== SECTION HEADINGS & SYNOPSES ========== ]]

# ACT ONE

= One-line synopsis for Act One (synopsis follows section heading when written this way.)

## SEQUENCE A

= Deeper synopsis under a level-2 section.

### BEAT — INTRO

= Level-three section with synopsis.


[[ ========== BRACKET NOTES ========== ]]

[[ This is a Fountain NOTE — double brackets, often used for editor comments. ]]

INT. AFTER NOTE - DAY

[[ Notes can appear between other elements if surrounded by blank lines as the spec expects for body notes. ]]


[[ ========== BONEYARD (OMITTED FROM OUTPUT) ========== ]]

/* One-line boneyard can open and close on the same row. */

/*

Everything between slash-stars is boneyard — omitted from screenplay output in most renderers.

INT. THIS LINE LOOKS LIKE A SLUG - BUT IT IS INSIDE BONEYARD

It can span many lines.

*/

INT. BACK IN THE REAL SCRIPT - DAY

Visible action after boneyard closes.


[[ ========== PAGE BREAK ========== ]]

===

[[ Three equals on their own line — page break. ]]

INT. AFTER PAGE BREAK - DAY


[[ ========== SYNOPSIS LINE (BODY) ========== ]]

= Standalone synopsis line not tied to a # section header (when used alone in body context per your parser).


[[ ========== SCENE NUMBERS (slug suffix) ========== ]]

INT. NUMBERED AGAIN - DUSK #42#

[[ Scene numbers in hashes at end of slug; may be stripped from element text in structured export. ]]


[[ ========== FORCED SCENE PREFIXES & SPECIAL CASES ========== ]]

!This line is forced ACTION, not dialogue.

.INT. ANOTHER FORCED SLUG - MAGIC HOUR


[[ ========== WHITESPACE & DELIMITERS ========== ]]

INT. FINAL BEAT - NIGHT

One blank line above separates blocks.

Two blank lines above can change pacing; Fountain still uses blank lines as structural separators.

MAN
Use a blank line after dialogue before the next element.

> FADE OUT.

[[ Whitespace-only lines (spaces/tabs only) are not emitted as standalone Action in this stack (Phase 4.6); they still affect dialogue-block continuation when inside dialogue. ]]

[[ End of reference. For full normative rules see https://fountain.io/syntax/ ]]
